<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>Drivers brought traffic to a halt as they marched to the mayoral building in Germiston to hand over the memorandum.They vowed they would go back to the streets if their demands were not addressed.They said Masina should step down within 30 days.The N3 highway leading to Gillooly’s interchange was blocked and commuters were left stranded at taxi ranks.Kempton Park taxi operators led a protest to Germiston and delivered a memorandum complaining about the lack of service delivery by the City. They complained about the road infrastructure and taxi ranks and said were in a bad state.They blamed Masina for the slow construction of the Ekurhuleni BRT system.There was a large presence of police in Germiston and the building was barricaded.Themba Gadebe, spokesman for the City of Ekurhuleni, accepted the memorandum on behalf of the MMC for Transport, Councillor Petrus Mabunda.“Mabunda assured delegation that the memorandum would be given urgent attention,” said Gadebe.He said Masina will meet with Santaco representatives today to find a solution.